DclMkYxOSUyRjI0JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbF9hY3Rpb25cdTAwMjZ1dG1fc291=
cmNlPWN1c3RvbWVyLmlvXHUwMDI2dXRtX3Rlcm09ZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwiaW50ZXJ=
uYWwiOiJmNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJsaW5rX2lkIjo5NjYwMTB9/b45a83695b7ccd5d4=
71f7b7da4034ba8e745646a7af7e5f2ae045d427fa336dc" style=3D"color:#d40000;tex=
t-decoration:none;font-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf"><u>reported</u> </a>that =
=E2=80=9CZaslav was examining several strategic options, ranging from selli=
ng assets to hiving off its Warner Bros. movie studio and Max streaming ser=
vice into a new company unburdened by most of the group=E2=80=99s current $=
39 billion net debt load.=E2=80=9D<br/> <br/>If that potential plan sounds =
familiar, it=E2=80=99s because some analysts and hedge fund managers sugges=
ted Disney should do something similar last year: essentially, put the decl=
ining TV assets and the debt on the corporate equivalent of a garbage barge=
 that could be floated away from the remaining growth assets, thus creating=
 a =E2=80=9Cclean=E2=80=9D company with a strong narrative. <b>Bob
Iger</b> ultimately decided not to do that <i>or</i> sell the TV networks o=
utright.<br/> <br/>But Zaslav, perhaps admitting that the grand plan to mas=
h up Discovery=E2=80=99s lowbrow reality shows with the prestige of HBO and=
 the Warner Bros. studio did not, in fact, turn into the stuff that dreams =
are made of, might find that path alluring. It=E2=80=99s now been three mon=
ths since the expiration of the Reverse Morris Trust rules allowed WBD to p=
ursue deals, and a week after his Sun Valley comments, where he all but beg=
ged the federal government for =E2=80=9Cderegulation, so companies can cons=
olidate and do what we need to to be even better.=E2=80=9D It=E2=80=99s cle=
ar he knows he needs to do <i>something</i>, and probably quickly.<br/></td=
